Using Markdown and Microsoft Copilot made prompt testing clearer and easier. Markdown helped organize ideas neatly, while Copilot simplified refining prompts. Together, they supported computational thinking by encouraging decomposition, abstraction, and pattern recognitionâ€”keeping Travel Planner prompts focused, structured, and free from confusion or unnecessary details.


